sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PalcA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A promoter that is inducible by alcohol, threonine can be used as an inducer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: DTU-Denmark-2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: from plasmid p82, CMB strain collection
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Compatible with the Plug'n'Play with DNA assembly standard

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: yA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The gene yA from Aspergillus nidulans encodes a p-diphenol oxidase (laccase) that converts a yellow pigment precursor to the mature green form. The green pigment is located in the walls of the conidia and protects the spores from damage by ultraviolet light. A yA mutant produces yellow spores.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: DTU-Denmark-2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Compatible with the Plug'n'Play assembly standard

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Monomeric red fluorescent protein (mRFP1) is a derivative of the red fluorescent protein cloned from Discosoma coral (DsRed) (1). The successful use of mRFP1 in Aspergillus nidulans has previously been described (2).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: DTU-Denmark-2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From p71-mRFP1 of the Center for Microbial Biotechnology plasmid collection at the Technical University of Denmark
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was designed for the Plug'n'Play with DNA assembly standard (RFC 80), therefore this part contains tails at the 5' and 3' ends as shown on the figure below. Please notice that mRFP1-TS is not the same as BBa_K678030 or BBa_K678031.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From the plasmid p71 from the Center for Microbial Biotechnology at the Technical University of Denmark plasmid collection.
